@tacigar 
> Disable the selection of span name or remote service name before the service name is selected.

i would go for this option, it's pretty drastic though and it it's bound to generate the same 'huh?' from users as not autocompleting it. Ideally there is some visual relationship between service name and span name that makes it clear that you cannot filter on the latter without first setting the former.

looks good. can you add a test to ITZipkinServer to make sure this isn't broken later?

```java
  @Test public void getTrace_spaceAfterTraceId() throws Exception {
    storage.accept(TRACE).execute();

    Response response = get("/api/v2/trace/" + TRACE.get(0).traceId() + " ");
    assertThat(response.isSuccessful()).isTrue();

    assertThat(response.body().bytes())
      .containsExactly(SpanBytesEncoder.JSON_V2.encodeList(TRACE));
  }
```

yeah threadfactorybuilder is overkill. go for 1. Also I remember this will
not work with self-tracing.. you can do something like this using your own
naming thread factory or with micrometer's

new NamedThreadFactory("zipkin-throttle-pool") {
  @Override public Thread newThread(Runnable runnable) {
    return super.newThread(new Runnable() {
      @Override public void run() {
        RequestContextCurrentTraceContext.setCurrentThreadNotRequestThread(true);
        runnable.run();
      }

      @Override public String toString() {
        return runnable.toString();
      }
    });
  }
},



