> Describe the Bug
>
> When setting up ES_CREDENTIALS_FILE to enable credentials file for
> zipkin-slim, a java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError:
> com/google/common/util/concurrent/ThreadFactoryBuilder is raised. The
> exception is from
> https://github.com/openzipkin/zipkin/blob/3aa6695bfdee6d0352a589ee10355b0fde705861/zipkin-server/src/main/java/zipkin2/server/internal/elasticsearch/ZipkinElasticsearchStorageConfiguration.java#L166
> which leverages guava ThreadFactoryBuilder to build a thread factory for
> credentials file refresher.
>
> I found that's becauseguava is excluded from slim.
>
> https://github.com/openzipkin/zipkin/blob/3aa6695bfdee6d0352a589ee10355b0fde705861/zipkin-server/pom.xml#L510
>
> There seem two paths to fix it.
>
>    1. Remove ThreadFactoryBuilder to get rid of guava dependency.
>    2. Add guava back to slim.
>
> I prefer the first approach. @adriancole <https://github.com/adriancole>
> WDYT?
